{
  "version": "2.0",
  "logging": {
    "applicationInsights": {
      "samplingSettings": {
        "isEnabled": true,
        "maxTelemetryItemsPerSecond": 20
      }
    }
  },
  "extensionBundle": {
    "id": "Microsoft.Azure.Functions.ExtensionBundle",
    "version": "[3.*, 4.0.0)"
  },
  "extensions": {
    "http": {
      "routePrefix": "api"
    }
  },
  "cors": {
    "allowedOrigins": ["*"],
    "supportCredentials": false
  }
}
The key part is the "cors" section at the bottom - this tells Azure Functions runtime to allow cross-origin requests.

Deploy
bash
git add api/host.json staticwebapp.config.json
git commit -m "Add CORS configuration for Azure Functions"
git push origin main
Why both files?

staticwebapp.config.json - For the Static Web App layer
api/host.json - For the Azure Functions runtime layer
Both are needed because Azure Static Web Apps have two layers that handle requests!

